name>weather</name>\\n    <description>Get current weather and forecasts via wttr.in or Open-Meteo. Use when: user asks about weather, temperature, or forecasts for any location. NOT for: historical weather data, severe weather alerts, or detailed meteorological analysis. No API key needed.</description>\\n    <location>~/AppData\\\\Roaming\\\\npm\\\\node_modules\\\\openclaw\\\\skills\\\\weather\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>api-design</name>\\n    <description>REST API design patterns and best practices. Use when: (1) designing APIs,\\n(2) reviewing API contracts, (3) implementing endpoints, (4) API versioning.\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\api-design\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>documentation</name>\\n    <description>Documentation best practices and patterns. Use when: (1) writing documentation,\\n(2) reviewing docs, (3) creating READMEs, (4) API documentation.\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\documentation\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>ecc-autoresearch</name>\\n    <description>Sichere autonome Forschung mit ECC-Framework.\\nWie autoresearch, aber mit ECC-Sicherheitsgarantien und Human-in-Loop.\\n\\nUse WHEN: Running autonomous AI research experiments with safety constraints.\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\ecc-autoresearch\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>grill-me</name>\\n    <description>Relentlessly interview the user about a plan or design until reaching shared understanding, resolving each branch of the decision tree. Use when user wants to stress-test a plan, get grilled on their design, mentions &quot;grill me&quot;, or before starting implementation to catch edge cases.</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\grill-me\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>plan-feature</name>\\n    <description>Turn a feature idea into a phased implementation plan using vertical slices (tracer bullets). Use when user wants to break down a feature, create an implementation plan, plan phases, or mentions &quot;tracer bullets&quot; or &quot;vertical slices&quot;.</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\plan-feature\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>python-patterns</name>\\n    <description>Python best practices and patterns. Use when: (1) writing Python code, \\n(2) reviewing Python, (3) debugging Python issues, (4) structuring Python projects.\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\python-patterns\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>refactoring</name>\\n    <description>Code refactoring patterns and techniques. Use when: (1) improving existing code,\\n(2) technical debt reduction, (3) code modernization, (4) performance optimization.\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\refactoring\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>secure-api-client</name>\\n    <description>A secure HTTP API client skill with built-in security controls.\\n\\nUse WHEN: Making API requests with proper authentication, rate limiting,\\ntimeout handling, and input validation.\\n\\nTrigger phrases: &quot;make API call&quot;, &quot;fetch data from API&quot;, &quot;secure HTTP request&quot;,\\n&quot;call REST API&quot;, &quot;API client request&quot;\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\secure-api-client\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>security-review</name>\\n    <description>Automated security analysis skill for code repositories (Python, PowerShell, JavaScript, and more).\\n\\nUse WHEN: Analyzing code for security vulnerabilities, reviewing repositories\\nfor security risks, auditing dependencies, or assessing execution safety.\\n\\nTrigger phrases: &quot;security audit&quot;, &quot;analyze security&quot;, &quot;security review&quot;,\\n&quot;check for vulnerabilities&quot;, &quot;is this code safe&quot;, &quot;security analysis&quot;,\\n&quot;audit repository&quot;, &quot;security check&quot;\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\security-review\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>tdd-loop</name>\\n    <description>Test-driven development with active red-green-refactor loop. Use when user wants to build features or fix bugs using TDD, mentions &quot;red-green-refactor&quot;, &quot;write a test first&quot;, or wants integration tests through public interfaces.</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\tdd-loop\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>testing-patterns</name>\\n    <description>Testing best practices and patterns. Use when: (1) writing tests, \\n(2) designing test strategy, (3) debugging test failures, (4) setting up test infrastructure.\\n</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\testing-patterns\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n  <skill>\\n    <name>write-a-prd</name>\\n    <description>Create a Product Requirements Document through interactive user interview, codebase exploration, and module design. Use when user wants to write a PRD, create product requirements, or plan a new feature from scratch.</description>\\n    <location>~/.openclaw\\\\workspace\\\\skills\\\\write-a-prd\\\\SKILL.md</location>\\n  </skill>\\n</available_skills>\",\n      \"skills\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"clawhub\",\n          \"requiredEnv\": []\n        },\n        {\n          \"name\": \"healthcheck\"\n\n[6839 more lines in file. Use offset=31 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775857519194}}
