{"type":"message","id":"2c35969f","parentId":"920215fa","timestamp":"2026-04-10T22:41:34.829Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Der Nutzer fragt, ob ich den Skill aktiviert habe. Ich habe den Skill erstellt und in das Verzeichnis gespeichert, aber ich habe ihn nicht in OpenClaw \"registriert\" oder aktiviert.\n\nIn OpenClaw werden Skills normalerweise über die registry/skills.yaml oder durch das Lesen der SKILL.md Datei aktiviert. Ich sollte prüfen, ob der Skill registriert werden muss oder ob er automatisch erkannt wird.\n\nLass mich die aktuelle skills.yaml prüfen und dann erklären, was noch nötig ist.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Nein, ich habe den Skill nur erstellt, aber noch nicht in OpenClaw registriert. Lass mich prüfen, wie wir ihn aktivieren..."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_gxgU8y8CuwnQZaWEQFBTzyT0","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/registry/skills.yaml"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":5409,"output":204,"cacheRead":142336,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":147949,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775860884198}}
{"type":"message","id":"7fd861ff","parentId":"2c35969f","timestamp":"2026-04-10T22:41:34.868Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_gxgU8y8CuwnQZaWEQFBTzyT0","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Skill Registry - Phase 2: Matt Pocock Enhancement\n# Auto-generiert aus skills/*/SKILL.md\n# Format: YAML 1.2\n\nversion: \"2.0\"\nlast_updated: \"2026-04-05T18:05:00+02:00\"\nauto_generated: false\ngenerator_version: \"2.0\"\n\n# Gesamtanzahl Skills\ncount: 15\n\nskills:\n  # ============================================\n  # PLANNING SKILLS (NEW - Matt Pocock Style)\n  # ============================================\n  - id: \"write-a-prd\"\n    name: \"write-a-prd\"\n    description: \"Create a Product Requirements Document through interactive user interview, codebase exploration, and module design. Use when user wants to write a PRD, create product requirements, or plan a new feature from scratch.\"\n    path: \"skills/write-a-prd\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/write-a-prd/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"planning\"\n    triggers: [\"write prd\", \"product requirements\", \"prd\", \"plan feature\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"interactive\"\n    \n  - id: \"grill-me\"\n    name: \"grill-me\"\n    description: \"Relentlessly interview the user about a plan or design until reaching shared understanding, resolving each branch of the decision tree. Use when user wants to stress-test a plan, get grilled on their design, mentions 'grill me', or before starting implementation to catch edge cases.\"\n    path: \"skills/grill-me\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/grill-me/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"planning\"\n    triggers: [\"grill me\", \"stress test\", \"review plan\", \"edge cases\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"interactive\"\n    \n  - id: \"plan-feature\"\n    name: \"plan-feature\"\n    description: \"Turn a feature idea into a phased implementation plan using vertical slices (tracer bullets). Use when user wants to break down a feature, create an implementation plan, plan phases, or mentions 'tracer bullets' or 'vertical slices'.\"\n    path: \"skills/plan-feature\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/plan-feature/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"planning\"\n    triggers: [\"plan feature\", \"break down\", \"implementation plan\", \"tracer bullets\", \"vertical slices\", \"phases\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"structured\"\n    \n  # ============================================\n  # DEVELOPMENT SKILLS\n  # ============================================\n  - id: \"tdd-loop\"\n    name: \"tdd-loop\"\n    description: \"Test-driven development with active red-green-refactor loop. Use when user wants to build features or fix bugs using TDD, mentions 'red-green-refactor', 'write a test first', or wants integration tests through public interfaces.\"\n    path: \"skills/tdd-loop\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/tdd-loop/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"development\"\n    triggers: [\"tdd\", \"red green refactor\", \"test first\", \"write test\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"matt-pocock-adapted\"\n    workflow_type: \"active-loop\"\n    related_skills: [\"testing-patterns\"]\n    \n  # ============================================\n  # ORIGINAL SKILLS\n  # ============================================\n  - id: \"example-weather\"\n    name: \"example-weather\"\n    description: \"Fetch weather data from external APIs\"\n    path: \"skills/example-weather\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/example-weather/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"external-api\"\n    triggers: [\"weather\", \"forecast\", \"temperature\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"secure-api-client\"\n    name: \"secure-api-client\"\n    description: \"Secure HTTP API client with built-in security controls\"\n    path: \"skills/secure-api-client\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/secure-api-client/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"security\"\n    triggers: [\"api\", \"http\", \"security\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"self-improving-andrew\"\n    name: \"self-improving-andrew\"\n    description: \"Self-improving agent that learns from corrections\"\n    path: \"skills/self-improving-andrew\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/self-improving-andrew/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"learning\"\n    triggers: [\"learning\", \"feedback\", \"correction\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"mission-control\"\n    name: \"mission-control\"\n    description: \"Command center for creating, managing, and deploying tools\"\n    path: \"skills/mission-control\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/mission-control/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"tool\", \"create\", \"deploy\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    \n  - id: \"mission-control-v2\"\n    name: \"mission-control-v2\"\n    description: \"Enhanced version of mission-control\"\n    path: \"skills/mission-control-v2\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/mission-control-v2/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: false\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"advanced tool\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    note: \"Contains node_modules\"\n    \n  # ECC Skills\n  - id: \"python-patterns\"\n    name: \"python-patterns\"\n    description: \"Python best practices and patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/python-patterns\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/python-patterns/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"language\"\n    triggers: [\"python\", \"pythonic\", \"py\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"security-review\"\n    name: \"security-review\"\n    description: \"Security-focused code review patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/security-review\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/security-review/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"security\"\n    triggers: [\"security\", \"vulnerability\", \"audit\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"testing-patterns\"\n    name: \"testing-patterns\"\n    description: \"Testing best practices and TDD patterns (static reference). Use when looking for testing patterns, test structure, or TDD theory. For active TDD workflow, use tdd-loop.\"\n    path: \"skills/testing-patterns\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/testing-patterns/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"quality\"\n    triggers: [\"test patterns\", \"testing theory\", \"tdd patterns\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    related_skills: [\"tdd-loop\"]\n    \n  - id: \"api-design\"\n    name: \"api-design\"\n    description: \"REST API design patterns and OpenAPI\"\n    path: \"skills/api-design\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/api-design/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"architecture\"\n    triggers: [\"api\", \"rest\", \"endpoint\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"documentation\"\n    name: \"documentation\"\n    description: \"Documentation best practices\"\n    path: \"skills/documentation\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/documentation/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"communication\"\n    triggers: [\"document\", \"readme\", \"docs\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"refactoring\"\n    name: \"refactoring\"\n    description: \"Code refactoring patterns\"\n    path: \"skills/refactoring\"\n    skill_file: \"skills/refactoring/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"quality\"\n    triggers: [\"refactor\", \"clean up\", \"optimize\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"adapted-from-ecc\"\n    \n  - id: \"second-brain\"\n    name: \"second-brain\"\n    description: \"PARA-based knowledge management for OpenClaw sessions\"\n    path: \"second-brain\"\n    skill_file: \"second-brain/SKILL.md\"\n    has_frontmatter: true\n    category: \"tooling\"\n    triggers: [\"second brain\", \"para\", \"knowledge\", \"obsidian\", \"sync\"]\n    status: \"active\"\n    source: \"custom\"\n\n# ============================================\n# CATEGORY INDEX\n# ============================================\ncategories:\n  planning: [\"write-a-prd\", \"grill-me\", \"plan-feature\"]\n  development: [\"tdd-loop\"]\n  external-api: [\"example-weather\"]\n  security: [\"secure-api-client\", \"security-review\"]\n  learning: [\"self-improving-andrew\"]\n  tooling: [\"mission-control\", \"mission-control-v2\", \"second-brain\"]\n  language: [\"python-patterns\"]\n  quality: [\"testing-patterns\", \"refactoring\"]\n  architecture: [\"api-design\"]\n  communication: [\"documentation\"]\n\n# ============================================\n# WORKFLOW CHAINS\n# ============================================\nworkflow_chains:\n  feature_development:\n    description: \"Complete workflow from idea to implementation\"\n    steps:\n      - write-a-prd\n      - grill-me\n      - plan-feature\n      - tdd-loop\n    optional:\n      - testing-patterns\n      \n  quick_feature:\n    description: \"Fast track for small features\"\n    steps:\n      - plan-feature\n      - tdd-loop\n\n# ============================================\n# AGENT ASSIGNMENTS\n# ============================================\nagent_assignments:\n  andrew-main:\n    - write-a-prd\n    - grill-me\n    - plan-feature\n    - tdd-loop\n    - example-weather\n    - secure-api-client\n    - self-improving-andrew\n    - mission-control\n    - python-patterns\n    - security-review\n    - testing-patterns\n    - api-design\n    - documentation\n    - refactoring\n    - second-brain\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775860894863}}
{"type":"message","id":"b5912c89","parentId":"7fd861ff","timestamp":"2026-04-10T22:41:53.879Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Der Skill ist in der registry/skills.yaml noch nicht eingetragen. Ich muss ihn hinzufügen, damit er aktiviert wird. Aber der Skill liegt ja im vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/, nicht im skills/ Ordner.\n\nIch sollte den Skill entweder:\n1. Nach skills/ verschieben und in skills.yaml registrieren\n2. Oder erklären, dass er dort liegt und manuell geladen werden muss\n\nDa der Nutzer den Skill explizit im vault-archive haben wollte, sollte ich vorschlagen, ihn entweder dorthin zu lassen (manuell nutzbar) oder nach skills/ zu verschieben (automatisch aktiviert).","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Nein, der Skill ist noch nicht in der Registry eingetragen. Er liegt im vault-archive, aber OpenClaw lädt Skills nur aus `workspace/skills/` oder wenn sie in `registry/skills.yaml` registriert sind.\n\n**Zwei Optionen:**\n\n**Option A: Skill nach `skills/` verschieben** (empfohlen für Aktivierung)\n```\nworkspace/skills/safe-migration/\n├── SKILL.md\n└── scripts/\n    └── SafeMigration.psm1\n```\n\nDann wird er automatisch erkannt.\n\n**Option B: In Registry eintragen** (aktueller Ort behalten)\nEintrag in `registry/skills.yaml` mit absolutem Pfad:\n```yaml\n- id: \"safe-migration\"\n  name: \"safe-migration\"\n  path: \"vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/migration-skill\"\n```\n\n**Option C: Manuell nutzen** (keine Aktivierung nötig)\nDu importierst das PowerShell-Modul manuell:\n```powershell\nImport-Module \"C:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\vault-archive\\Main_Obsidian_Vault\\migration-skill\\scripts\\SafeMigration.psm1\"\n```\n\n**Was bevorzugst du?**\n- A: Verschieben nach skills/ (automatisch aktiv)\n- B: Registry-Eintrag (aktueller Ort bleibt)\n- C: Manuell nutzen (keine Änderung)"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":146263,"output":0,"c