{"type":"message","id":"f64f83d6","parentId":"ab5bc33a","timestamp":"2026-04-11T00:47:10.389Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_syJscBqFHj06RGFCuE1UO4UX","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw System Analysis - Overview\n\n> **Generated by**: Level 0 Overview Agent (overview-architect)  \n> **Date**: Analysis Phase  \n> **Source**: openclaw-complete-manifest.md  \n> **Purpose**: Context briefings for Level 1 Domain Expert Agents\n\n---\n\n## 1. SYSTEM MAP\n\n### 1.1 High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           OPENCLAW AI AGENT SYSTEM                          │\n│                              (Agent-ID: andrew-main)                        │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐         │\n│  │   CHANNELS      │    │   SUB-AGENTS    │    │   EXTERNAL      │         │\n│  │                 │    │                 │    │   SERVICES      │         │\n│  │ • webchat       │◄──►│ • architect     │    │                 │         │\n│  │ • terminal      │    │ • planner       │◄──►│ • Gemini Search │         │\n│  │ • Telegram      │    │ • code-reviewer │    │ • wttr.in       │         │\n│  │                 │    │ • security      │    │ • Open-Meteo    │         │\n│  └────────┬────────┘    │ • python-rev    │    │ • GitHub        │         │\n│           │             │ • knowledge-cur │    │ • Obsidian      │         │\n│           │             └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘         │\n│           │                                                                 │\n│           ▼                                                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                     NODE.JS/TYPESCRIPT CORE                          │   │\n│  │  (OpenClaw Gateway, Session Management, Tool Integration)            │   │\n│  └────────┬──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┘   │\n│           │                              │                                 │\n│           ▼                              ▼                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────┐                         │\n│  │  RUST ECC CRATES │          │  REGISTRY SYSTEM │                         │\n│  │                  │          │                  │                         │\n│  │ • ecc-runtime    │          │ • agents.yaml    │                         │\n│  │ • memory-compact │          │ • skills.yaml    │                         │\n│  │ • tool-registry  │          │ • hooks.yaml     │                         │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘          └────────┬─────────┘                         │\n│           │                             │                                  │\n│           │    ┌────────────────────────┘                                  │\n│           │    │                                                            │\n│           ▼    ▼                                                            │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                      AUTOMATION & MEMORY LAYER                       │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │   │\n│  │  │   HOOKS      │  │ POWERSHELL   │  │ SECOND BRAIN │              │   │\n│  │  │              │  │              │  │              │              │   │\n│  │  │ • session-   │  │ • sync       │  │ • PARA       │              │   │\n│  │  │   start      │  │ • permissions│  │   structure  │              │   │\n│  │  │ • session-   │  │ • backup     │  │ • Obsidian   │              │   │\n│  │  │   end        │  │              │  │   sync       │              │   │\n│  │  │ • review-    │  │              │  │              │              │   │\n│  │  │   post-exec  │  │              │  │              │              │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘              │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.2 Data Flow Diagram\n\n```\nUser Request → Channel Handler → Session Manager → Skill Registry Lookup\n                                                    │\n                    ┌───────────────────────────────┼───────────────┐\n                    │                               │               │\n                    ▼                               ▼               ▼\n            Sub-Agent Spawn                  Tool Execution    Memory Log\n                    │                               │               │\n                    ▼                               ▼               ▼\n            ACP Runtime                    Rust Tool Registry  Daily Logs\n            (if external)                        │            (memory/)\n                                                 ▼\n                                          ECC Runtime\n                                          (Conversation)\n                                                 │\n                                                 ▼\n                                          Hook Trigger\n                                                 │\n                    ┌────────────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n                    │                            │                    │\n                    ▼                            ▼                    ▼\n            Session-End Hook           Review Post-Exec      Second Brain Sync\n                    │                     Hook (cron: 5min)\n                    ▼\n            Memory Compaction\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. DOMAIN BOUNDARIES\n\n### 2.1 Domain Overview Table\n\n| Domain | Directory | Primary Language | Test Count | Key Responsibility |\n|--------|-----------|------------------|------------|-------------------|\n| **Pair A: Rust ECC** | `crates/` | Rust | 60+ | Core runtime, memory, tools |\n| **Pair B: Node.js Core** | Gateway root | TypeScript | Unknown | Session, channels, integration |\n| **Pair C: YAML Registry** | `registry/` | YAML | N/A | Configuration, agent/skill/hook defs |\n| **Pair D: PowerShell + Hooks** | `hooks/`, `*.ps1` | PowerShell/Markdown | N/A | Automation, event handlers |\n| **Pair E: Second Brain** | `second-brain/`, `memory/` | Markdown | N/A | Knowledge management, logging |\n\n### 2.2 Interface Boundaries\n\n```\n┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         INTERFACE DEFINITIONS                           │\n├────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                         │\n│  Interface A-B: Rust Crates ↔ Node.js Core                             │\n│  ───────────────────────────────────────────                            │\n│  • FFI bindings or WASM (not specified in manifest)                    │\n│  • Tool Registry exposes tools to TypeScript gateway                   │\n│  • ECC Runtime manages conversation state                              │\n│  • Memory Compaction triggered by session-end                          │\n│                                                                         │\n│  Interface B-C: Node.js Core ↔ YAML Registry                           │\n│  ───────────────────────────────────────────                            │\n│  • agents.yaml loaded at startup for sub-agent definitions             │\n│  • skills.yaml scanned before each response                            │\n│  • hooks.yaml triggers handlers at lifecycle events                    │\n│                                                                         │\n│  Interface B-D: Node.js Core ↔ Hooks/PowerShell                        │\n│  ───────────────────────────────────────────                            │\n│  • session:start → hooks/session-start.md                              │\n│  • session:end → hooks/session-end.md                                  │\n│  • review:post_execution → hooks/review-post-execution.md              │\n│  • Cron triggers PowerShell sync scripts                               │\n│                                                                         │\n│  Interface B-E: Node.js Core ↔ Second Brain/Memory                     │\n│  ───────────────────────────────────────────                            │\n│  • Daily logs written to memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md                          │\n│  • MEMORY.md updated with curated insights                             │\n│  • Second Brain sync via PowerShell (5-min cron)                       │\n│                                                                         │\n│  Interface C-D: Registry ↔ Hooks                                       │\n│  ───────────────────────────────────────────                            │\n│  • hooks.yaml defines triggers                                         │\n│  • Hook handlers in hooks/ directory                                   │\n│  • Hook engine implementation unclear                                  │\n│                                                                         │\n└────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. LEVEL 1 DOMAIN BRIEFINGS\n\n### 3.1 PAIR A: Rust ECC Framework\n\n#### Domain Intention\nThe Rust ECC (Everything Claw Code) Framework provides the core runtime infrastructure for the OpenClaw agent:\n- **Conversation Runtime**: Manages AI conversation state and context\n- **Memory Compaction**: Handles session cleanup and state optimization\n- **Tool Registry**: Manages available tools and their execution\n- **Security Layer**: Permission framework and safe execution environment\n\n#### Files Belonging to This Domain\n\n```\ncrates/\n├── ecc-runtime/              # Conversation Runtime\n│   ├── src/\n│   └── tests/ (9 passing)\n├── memory-compaction/        # Session Compaction\n│   ├── src/\n│   └── tests/ (22 passing)\n├── tool-registry/            # Tool Management\n│   ├── src/\n│   └── tests/ (11 passing)\n└── (skills)/                 # Security, API Client\n    ├── src/\n    └── tests/ (22 passing)\n```\n\n#### Key Interfaces to Other Domains\n\n| Interface | Partner Domain | Description |\n|-----------|---------------|-------------|\n| Tool API | Node.js Core | Tools exposed to TypeScript gateway |\n| Session State | Node.js Core | Conversation context shared with session manager |\n| Compaction Trigger | Hooks | session:end hook triggers memory compaction |\n| MCP Adapter | Node.js Core | In development (mentioned 2026-04-02) |\n\n#### Known Issues from Manifest\n- **MCP Integration**: Listed as \"in Arbeit\" (in progress) as of 2026-04-02\n- **Test Coverage**: 60+ tests passing, but unclear if critical paths are covered\n- **Hook Integration**: Unclear if Rust runtime properly triggers session-end compaction\n\n#### Questions for Domain Agents\n1. How does the Rust runtime communicate with the Node.js gateway? (FFI? WASM? IPC?)\n2. Are the 60 tests integration tests or unit tests?\n3. Is the MCP adapter complete or partially implemented?\n\n---\n\n### 3.2 PAIR B: Node.js/TypeScript Core\n\n#### Domain Intention\nThe Node.js/TypeScript Core is the OpenClaw Gateway that orchestrates:\n- **Session Management**: User session lifecycle and state\n- **Channel Handlers**: webchat, terminal, Telegram integration\n- **Tool Integration**: Calling tools from registry\n- **Sub-Agent Spawning**: Launching specialized agents (architect, planner, etc.)\n- **ACP Runtime**: External agent communication protocol\n\n#### Files Belonging to This Domain\n\n```\nC:\\Users\\andre\\.openclaw\\workspace\\\n├── .openclaw/                # OpenClaw internal config\n│   └── (internal Config)\n├── AGENTS.md                 # Workspace conventions\n├── BOOTSTRAP.md              # First-time setup (delete after)\n├── HEARTBEAT.md              # Periodic tasks definition\n├── IDENTITY.md               # Agent identity (Name, Emoji, Vibe)\n├── TOOLS.md                  # Local tool configurations\n│\n├── agents/                   # Sub-Agent definitions (6 agents)\n│   ├── architect.md\n│   ├── code-reviewer.md\n│   ├── knowledge-curator.md\n│   ├── planner.md\n│   ├── python-reviewer.md\n│   └── security-reviewer.md\n│\n└── docs/                     # Documentation\n    ├── ADR-001-no-claw-discovery.md\n    └── (weitere)\n```\n\n#### Key Interfaces to Other Domains\n\n| Interface | Partner Domain | Description |\n|-----------|---------------|-------------|\n| Tool Calls | Rust ECC | Invokes tools from Rust registry |\n| Config Load | YAML Registry | Reads agents.yaml, skills.yaml, hooks.yaml |\n| Hook Trigger | Hooks/PowerShell | Triggers lifecycle hooks |\n| Memory Write | Second Brain | Writes to memory/ directory |\n| Sync Trigger | PowerShell | Initiates Second Brain sync |\n\n#### Known Issues from Manifest\n- **\"edit failed\" Bug**: `[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText` - CRITICAL\n- **Tool Parameter Mismatch**: Documentation says `new_string` but error says `newText`\n- **Hook Timing**: Unclear if hooks interfere with tool calls\n- **Channel Abstraction**: Potential duplicate logic between webchat/terminal/Telegram\n\n#### Questions for Domain Agents\n1. Where is the tool invocation code that produces the \"edit failed\" error?\n2. Is there a mismatch between documented parameters (`new_string`) and actual parameters (`newText`)?\n3. How do hooks interact with the tool execution flow?\n\n---\n\n### 3.3 PAIR C: YAML/Registry System\n\n#### Domain Intention\nThe YAML/Registry System provides declarative configuration for:\n- **Agent Registry**: Sub-agent definitions and triggers\n- **Skill Registry**: Available skills and their metadata\n- **Hook Registry**: Event handlers and their triggers\n- **Cron Configuration**: Scheduled task definitions\n\n#### Files Belonging to This Domain\n\n```\nregistry/\n├── agents.yaml               # Agent definitions & triggers\n├── skills.yaml               # Skill registry (18 skills)\n└── hooks.yaml                # Hook definitions\n```\n\n**Related YAML Configs:**\n- `HEARTBEAT.md` - Periodic tasks (not YAML but structured config)\n- `.openclaw/` - Internal configuration\n\n#### Key Interfaces to Other Domains\n\n| Interface | Partner Domain | Description |\n|-----------|---------------|-------------|\n| Agent Spawn | Node.js Core | agents.yaml defines sub-agents |\n| Skill Lookup | Node.js Core | skills.yaml scanned before responses |\n| Hook Trigger | Hooks | hooks.yaml maps events to handlers |\n| Cron Jobs | PowerShell | Scheduled tasks trigger scripts |\n\n#### Known Issues from Manifest\n- **Hook Activation**: Unclear if hooks.yaml actually triggers anything\n- **Registry Usage**: Not verified if all registry entries are actively used\n- **Config/Code Sync**: Potential inconsistency between YAML and implementation\n- **Hardcoded Values**: Some values may be hardcoded that should be in config\n\n#### Questions for Domain Agents\n1. Does hooks.yaml actually trigger the handlers in hooks/ directory?\n2. Are all 18 skills in skills.yaml actively used?\n3. Is there a schema validation for the YAML files?\n\n---\n\n### 3.4 PAIR D: PowerShell Automation + Hooks\n\n#### Domain Intention\nThe PowerShell Automation + Hooks layer provides:\n- **Hook Engine**: Event-driven handlers for session lifecycle\n- **Sync Automation**: Second Brain synchronization (5-minute cron)\n- **Permission Management**: File system permission fixes\n- **Backup Operations**: Data backup and recovery\n\n#### Files Belonging to This Domain\n\n```\nhooks/\n├── session-start.md          # Session start handler\n├── session-end.md            # Session end handler\n└── review-post-execution.md  # Post-execution review handler\n\nsecond-brain/scripts/\n└── sync-openclaw-to-secondbrain.ps1  # Sync script\n\n(PowerShell scripts mentioned but not fully listed)\n```\n\n#### Key Interfaces to Other Domains\n\n| Interface | Partner Domain | Description |\n|-----------|---------------|-------------|\n| Hook Trigger | YAML Registry | hooks.yaml defines when to trigger |\n| Hook Handler | Node.js Core | Gateway calls hook handlers |\n| Sync Target | Second Brain | Syncs to PARA structure |\n| Cron Trigger | Registry | 5-minute cron job defined somewhere |\n\n#### Known Issues from Manifest\n- **Hook Execution**: Unclear if hooks are actually triggered\n- **Error Recovery**: Missing error recovery in sync operations\n- **Race Conditions**: Potential race conditions in sync operations\n- **Session-End Reliability**: Unclear if session-end hooks always run\n- **Edit Failed Connection**: Possible relation to hook timing\n\n#### Questions for Domain Agents\n1. Is there a hook engine implementation, or are hooks just markdown files?\n2. Does the 5-minute cron job actually exist and run?\n3. Are there race conditions between sync operations?\n\n---\n\n### 3.5 PAIR E: Second Brain + Memory System\n\n#### Domain Intention\nThe Second Brain + Memory System provides:\n- **PARA Structure**: Projects, Areas, Resources, Archive organization\n- **Daily Logging**: Session logs in memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md\n- **Curated Memory**: Long-term insights in MEMORY.md\n- **Self-Improvement**: Feedback loop from corrections\n- **Obsidian Integration**: Sync with Obsidian vault\n\n#### Files Belonging to This Domain\n\n```\nmemory/\n├── 2026-03-22.md             # Daily logs\n├── 2026-03-23.md\n├── 2026-03-26.md\n├── 2026-03-28.md\n├── 2026-03-30.md\n├── 2026-03-31.md\n├── 2026-04-02.md\n├── self-improving/           # Feedback logs\n├── sessions/                 # Session states\n└── templates/                # Log templates\n\nsecond-brain/\n├── 1-Projects/\n│   └── active/\n│       └── openclaw-ecc-integration/\n├── 2-Areas/\n│   ├── healthcheck/\n│   ├── learning/\n│   └── maintenance/\n├── 3-Resources/\n│   ├── rust/\n│   ├── architecture/\n│   └── security/\n├── 4-Archive/\n├── Templates/\n└── scripts/\n    └── sync-openclaw-to-secondbrain.ps1\n```\n\n#### Key Interfaces to Other Domains\n\n| Interface | Partner Domain | Description |\n|-----------|---------------|-------------|\n| Log Write | Node.js Core | Gateway writes daily logs |\n| Sync Source | PowerShell | Sync script copies to Second Brain |\n| Cron Trigger | Registry | 5-minute sync cron job |\n| Memory Read | Node.js Core | Session startup reads memory |\n\n#### Known Issues from Manifest\n- **Sync Frequency**: 5-minute sync may be overkill\n- **Duplicate Information**: Potential duplicates across files\n- **Template Usage**: Unclear if templates are used consistently\n- **Learning Loop**: Not verified if system actually learns from corrections\n- **Daily Log Utility**: Unclear if daily logs are actually useful\n\n#### Questions for Domain Agents\n1. Is the 5-minute sync frequency justified?\n2. Are there duplicates between MEMORY.md and daily logs?\n3. Does the self-improving feedback loop actually work?\n\n---\n\n## 4. KNOWN ISSUES FROM MANIFEST\n\n### 4.1 Critical Issues\n\n| Issue | Domain | Description | First Mentioned |\n|-------|--------|-------------|-----------------|\n| **\"edit failed\" Bug** | Node.js Core | `[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText` | Manifest Section 7.3 |\n| Parameter Mismatch | Node.js Core | Documentation says `new_string`, error says `newText` | Tool-Usage Rules |\n\n### 4.2 In-Progress Work\n\n| Work Item | Domain | Status | Date |\n|-----------|--------|--------|------|\n| MCP Adapter | Rust ECC | \"in Arbeit\" (in progress) | 2026-04-02 |\n| Tailscale Setup | Infrastructure | \"In Einrichtung\" | Manifest |\n| whisper-local-stt | Skills | \"Code fertig, Setup ausstehend\" | Section 3.1 |\n\n### 4.3 Potential Issues (Unverified)\n\n| Issue | Domain | Evidence |\n|-------|--------|----------|\n| Hook Activation | Hooks/PowerShell | hooks.yaml exists but activation unclear |\n| Registry Usage | YAML Registry | Not verified if all entries used |\n| Channel Duplication | Node.js Core | 3 channels may have duplicate logic |\n| Sync Race Conditions | PowerShell | Concurrent sync operations possible |\n| Memory Recall | Second Brain | `memory_search` tool mentioned but not verified |\n\n### 4.4 Documented Workarounds\n\nFrom MEMORY.md (PowerShell Best Practices):\n1. Variable Interpolation: Use `${UserName}:(OI)(CI)F` with curly braces\n2. Permission Order: `takeown` → `icacls` → Copy → Final permissions\n3. ASCII-Only Output: No emojis on German Windows\n4. Reserved Variables: Avoid `$host`, `$input`, `$pwd`\n5. Locale-Independent: Use `$env:USERNAME` or SIDs\n\n---\n\n## 5. ORPHANED COMPONENTS\n\n### 5.1 Potentially Orphaned Files\n\n| File/Directory | Location | Why Orphaned | Suggested Connection |\n|----------------|----------|--------------|---------------------|\n| `BOOTSTRAP.md` | Root | \"löschen nach Setup\" (delete after setup) | One-time use file |\n| `safe-file-ops/SKILL.md` | skills/ | Not in 18-skill list | Verify if used |\n| `whisper-local-stt/SKILL.md` | skills/ | \"Setup ausstehend\" | Incomplete feature |\n| `docs/ADR-001-no-claw-discovery.md` | docs/ | Only ADR mentioned | Check for more ADRs |\n\n### 5.2 Orphaned References\n\n| Reference | Found In | Points To | Status |\n|-----------|----------|-----------|--------|\n| `memory_search` tool | Manifest Section 7.4 | Unknown implementation | Tool mentioned but not in registry |\n| `sessions_spawn` | Manifest Section 7.7 | ACP Runtime | Implementation unclear |\n| `subagents`/`agents_list` | Manifest Section 7.7 | Node.js Core | Should not be used per manifest |\n\n### 5.3 Unclear Connections\n\n| Component | Expected Connection | Actual Status |\n|-----------|---------------------|---------------|\n| Hook Engine | Should bridge hooks.yaml → handlers | Implementation unclear |\n| Cron Jobs | Should trigger PowerShell scripts | Only 5-min sync mentioned |\n| ACP Runtime | Should spawn external agents | Mentioned but not detailed |\n| MCP Adapter | Should integrate with MCP | \"In Arbeit\" (in progress) |\n\n---\n\n## 6. DEPENDENCY GRAPH\n\n### 6.1 Component Dependencies\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        DEPENDENCY GRAPH                                  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                          │\n│  Level 0: Runtime (Node.js Gateway)                                      │\n│  ─────────────────────────────────                                       │\n│  Depends on: Registry (agents.yaml, skills.yaml, hooks.yaml)             │\n│  Depends on: Rust ECC (tool-registry, ecc-runtime)                       │\n│  Triggers: Hooks (session-start, session-end)                            │\n│  Writes to: Memory (daily logs), Second Brain (via sync)                 │\n│                                                                          │\n│  Level 1: Rust ECC Crates                                                │\n│  ─────────────────────────                                               │\n│  ecc-runtime → (no internal deps listed)                                 │\n│  memory-compaction → (no internal deps listed)                           │\n│  tool-registry → (no internal deps listed)                               │\n│  All crates → Exposed to Node.js Gateway                                 │\n│                                                                          │\n│  Level 1: Registry                                                       │\n│  ─────────────────                                                       │\n│  agents.yaml → Read by Node.js Gateway                                   │\n│  skills.yaml → Read by Node.js Gateway (before each response)            │\n│  hooks.yaml → Should trigger handlers (connection unclear)               │\n│                                                                          │\n│  Level 1: Hooks + PowerShell                                             │\n│  ───────────────────────────                                             │\n│  hooks/*.md → Triggered by Gateway? Hook Engine?                         │\n│  *.ps1 → Triggered by Cron jobs?                                         │\n│  sync script → Writes to Second Brain                                    │\n│                                                                          │\n│  Level 1: Second Brain + Memory                                          │\n│  ──────────────────────────────                                          │\n│  memory/*.md → Written by Gateway, read at startup                       │\n│  second-brain/* → Synced from workspace via PowerShell                   │\n│                                                                          │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 6.2 Circular Dependency Check\n\nNo obvious circular dependencies detected, but potential issues:\n1. **Gateway ↔ Hooks**: Gateway triggers hooks, hooks may call Gateway functions\n2. **Memory ↔ Gateway**: Gateway writes memory, memory influences Gateway behavior\n3. **Sync ↔ Runtime**: Sync may run while runtime is active (race condition)\n\n---\n\n## 7. SUMMARY FOR LEVEL 1 AGENTS\n\n### 7.1 Priority Focus Areas\n\n| Priority | Domain | Focus |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| P0 | Node.js Core | **\"edit failed\" bug** - Parameter mismatch investigation |\n| P1 | Hooks/PowerShell | Verify hook engine actually triggers handlers |\n| P1 | YAML Registry | Verify registry entries are actively used |\n| P2 | Rust ECC | Check MCP adapter status and integration |\n| P2 | Second Brain | Verify sync frequency is justified |\n| P3 | All | Look for duplicate logic and consolidation opportunities |\n\n### 7.2 Cross-Domain Concerns\n\n1. **Hook Integration**: How do hooks.yaml, hook handlers, and the gateway interact?\n2. **Tool Parameter Flow**: Where does the `new_string` → `newText` mismatch occur?\n3. **Sync Timing**: Does the 5-minute cron interfere with active sessions?\n4. **Memory Recall**: Does `memory_search` tool exist and work?\n\n### 7.3 Questions Requiring Operator Input\n\n1. Is the \"edit failed\" error reproducible? When does it occur?\n2. Are hooks currently working, or is the hook engine not implemented?\n3. Is the MCP adapter in progress or abandoned?\n4. Should the 5-minute sync frequency be adjusted?\n\n---\n\n*End of Overview Analysis*  \n*Generated for Level 1 Domain Expert Agents*\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775868430382}}
{"type":"message","id":"4029992e","parentId":"f64f83d6","timestamp":"2026-04-11T00:48:12.071Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wow, das ist eine sehr detaillierte System-Architektur-Analyse! Lass mich die wichtigsten Punkte extrahieren und prüfen, welche der anderen 9 Dateien relevant sind.\n\nDie analysis-overview.md zeigt:\n1. Das OpenClaw System hat 5 \"Domains\":\n   - Rust ECC Framework (crates/)\n   - Node.js/TypeScript Core (Gateway)\n   - YAML/Registry System (registry/)\n   - PowerShell Automation + Hooks (hooks/, scripts/)\n   - Second Brain + Memory System (memory/, second-brain/)\n\n2. Bekannte kritische Issues:\n   - \"edit failed\" Bug (Parameter mismatch: new_string vs newText)\n   - MCP Adapter \"in Arbeit\"\n   - Hook Activation unklar\n   - Registry Usage unverifiziert\n\n3. Die anderen Dateien im Ordner scheinen zu sein:\n   - phase1-findings-*.md für jede Domain (5 Dateien)\n   - phase2-connections.md (Verbindungen zwischen Domains)\n   - phase3-recommendations.md (Empfehlungen)\n   - action-items-prioritized.md (Priorisierte Aktionen)\n   - bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md (Detail-Analyse des Edit-Bugs)\n\nDas ist eine sehr wertvolle technische Dokumentation! Ich sollte dem User zeigen, was hier vorhanden ist und welche Dateien am wichtigsten sind.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Das ist eine **umfassende System-Architektur-Analyse**! Hier ist die Zusammenfassung:\n\n---\n\n## Was ist das?\n\nEine **5-Phasen-Analyse** des OpenClaw-Systems:\n\n| Phase | Datei | Inhalt |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| **Phase 0** | analysis-overview.md | System-Übersicht (30 KB) |\n| **Phase 1** | 5x \"findings\" | Detail-Analyse pro Domain |\n| **Phase 2** | phase2-connections.md | Verbindungen zwischen Domains |\n| **Phase 3** | phase3-recommendations.md | Empfehlungen (28 KB) |\n| **Actions** | action-items-prioritized.md | Priorisierte ToDos (15 KB) |\n| **Bugfix** | bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md | Edit-Tool Bug Analyse (10 KB) |\n\n---\n\n## Die 5 Domains (im System)\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│  A: Rust ECC Framework (crates/)                        │\n│     → Core runtime, memory, tools (60+ Tests)          │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  B: Node.js/TypeScript Core (Gateway)                  │\n│     → Session, channels, tools (⚠️ \"edit failed\" Bug)  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  C: YAML Registry (registry/)                          │\n│     → agents.yaml, skills.yaml, hooks.yaml             │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  D: PowerShell + Hooks (hooks/, scripts/)              │\n│     → Automation, sync, event handlers                 │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  E: Second Brain + Memory (memory/, second-brain/)     │\n│     → PARA, daily logs, MEMORY.md                      │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Kritische Issues gefunden\n\n| Issue | Priorität | Wo dokumentiert |\n|-------|-----------|-----------------|\n| **\"edit failed\" Bug** | **P0 - KRITISCH** | bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md |\n| Parameter mismatch (new_string vs newText) | P0 | analysis-overview.md |\n| Hook Activation unklar | P1 | phase1-findings-powershell-hooks.md |\n| Registry Usage unverifiziert | P1 | phase1-findings-yaml-registry.md |\n| MCP Adapter \"in Arbeit\" | P2 | phase1-findings-rust-ecc.md |\n\n---\n\n## Meine Empfehlung\n\n**HIGH PRIORITY (sofort migrieren):**\n1. **bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md** (10 KB) - P0 Bugfix-Doku\n2. **phase3-recommendations.md** (28 KB) - Empfehlungen für Renovierung\n3. **action-items-prioritized.md** (15 KB) - ToDo-Liste\n\n**MEDIUM PRIORITY:**\n4. **phase1-findings-second-brain.md** (21 KB) - Für unser SecondBrain relevant\n5. **phase1-findings-yaml-registry.md** (21 KB) - Registry-Struktur\n\n**LOWER PRIORITY (technisch detailiert):**\n6. phase1-findings-nodejs-core.md (32 KB)\n7. phase1-findings-powershell-hooks.md (22 KB)\n8. phase1-findings-rust-ecc.md (18 KB)\n9. phase2-connections.md (18 KB)\n\n---\n\n**Soll ich starten mit:**\n- **A)** Den 3 HIGH PRIORITY Dateien (Bugfix, Recommendations, Action-Items)?\n- **B)** Oder eine bestimmte Datei deiner Wahl?\n- **C)** Oder erstmal die analysis-overview.md zusammenfassen?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":98441,"output":1126,"cacheRead":61440,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":161007,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775868430399}}
