{"type":"message","id":"4a628b7c","parentId":"0b8e0f0f","timestamp":"2026-04-11T00:51:13.306Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_JGvyVAoMMyBekTRjdygRtqoz","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Bugfix Analysis: `[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText`\n\n## Executive Summary\n\n**Severity**: Medium-High  \n**Type**: Parameter Naming Mismatch (Documentation vs. Implementation)  \n**Impact**: Tool calls fail when parameter name doesn't match expected schema  \n\n---\n\n## 1. Root Cause Analysis\n\n### 1.1 The Core Problem\n\nThe error message `Missing required parameter: newText` reveals a **parameter naming mismatch** between:\n\n| Source | Parameter Name | Context |\n|--------|---------------|---------|\n| **Manifest Documentation** | `new_string` | Section 5.3: \"NIE: `edit` ohne `new_string` Parameter\" |\n| **Error Message** | `newText` | Runtime validation error |\n| **Tool Schema (implied)** | Likely `new_string` | Based on convention |\n\n### 1.2 Evidence from Source Files\n\n**From `/mnt/okcomputer/upload/openclaw-complete-manifest.md` (Line 233):**\n```markdown\n**NIE**: `edit` ohne `new_string` Parameter\n```\n\n**From `/mnt/okcomputer/upload/openclaw-multi-agent-analysis-prompt.md`:**\n- Line 403: Scope explicitly mentions: `Diagnose '[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText'`\n- Line 409: Investigation path says: \"Identify where `new_string` parameter is missing\"\n\n### 1.3 Root Cause Hypothesis\n\nThe most likely explanations for this mismatch are:\n\n1. **Schema Translation Layer Issue**: \n   - The tool schema defines the parameter as `new_string` (snake_case, following conventions)\n   - A middleware/transformation layer converts snake_case to camelCase for some consumer\n   - The error validation occurs AFTER this transformation, expecting `newText`\n   - But the tool caller provides `new_string`, causing validation failure\n\n2. **Inconsistent Schema Versions**:\n   - Documentation references one version of the tool schema (`new_string`)\n   - Runtime uses a different version expecting `newText`\n   - This could happen during a migration or API update\n\n3. **Hook Interference** (as suggested in analysis prompt):\n   - The `review:post_execution` hook or another middleware may transform parameters\n\n[212 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775868673301}}
{"type":"message","id":"9202e707","parentId":"4a628b7c","timestamp":"2026-04-11T00:51:13.313Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_RVePguI9qxEaW1xkBwh6VnFk","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 03-04-2026\ntype: knowledge\ncategory: how-to\ntags: [how-to, bug, workaround, openclaw, edit-tool]\n---\n\n# How-To: Edit-Tool Workaround\n\n> **WICHTIG:** Das `edit` Tool hat einen bekannten Bug. Diese Anleitung zeigt den Workaround.\n\n## Das Problem\n\nDas `edit` Tool kann den `new_string` (oder `newText`) Parameter nicht korrekt an das Gateway übergeben.\n\n**Fehlermeldung:**\n```\n[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText (newText or new_string). \nSupply correct parameters before retrying.\n```\n\n**Ursache:**\n- Gateway validiert den Parameter, aber er kommt nie an\n- Getestet mit `new_string` und `newText` - beide funktionieren nicht\n- Problem liegt im Gateway-Level (`thread-bindings-*.js`)\n\n---\n\n## Die Lösung: Read + Write Pattern\n\nStatt `edit` zu verwenden, nutze **`read` + `write`**:\n\n### Schritt-für-Schritt\n\n1. **Datei lesen** - Aktuellen Inhalt holen\n2. **Inhalt ändern** - Modifikation durchführen  \n3. **Datei schreiben** - Neuen Inhalt zurückschreiben\n\n### Beispiel\n\n**❌ FALSCH (edit funktioniert nicht):**\n```markdown\nedit file.txt\nold_string: \"alt\"\nnew_string: \"neu\"\n```\n\n**✅ RICHTIG (read + write):**\n```markdown\n# Schritt 1: Lesen\n\n[88 more lines in file. Use offset=51 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775868673307}}
{"type":"message","id":"fbecf421","parentId":"9202e707","timestamp":"2026-04-11T00:51:31.080Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ich habe beide Dateien gefunden. Die bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md ist eine detaillierte technische Analyse des Bugs, während die edit-tool-workaround.md eine praktische Anleitung für den Workaround ist.\n\nSie sind komplementär:\n- bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md: Root Cause, technische Details, Hypothesen\n- edit-tool-workaround.md: Praktische Lösung für Nutzer\n\nKein Duplikat, aber verwandt. Sollten verlinkt werden.\n\nJetzt prüfe ich analysis-overview.md vs. openclaw-renovation.md","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Ergebnis 1: Edit-Tool Analyse**\n\n| Datei | Zweck | Status |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| **bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md** | Technische Root-Cause-Analyse | NOVEL - detaillierter |\n| **edit-tool-workaround.md** | Praktischer Workaround für User | Bereits vorhanden |\n\n**Verdict:** KEIN Duplikat - beide ergänzen sich (Analyse vs. Workaround)"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_sDeIeq0DbzhMmLIJdYctUE6M","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"C:/Users/andre/.openclaw/workspace/vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/Kimi_Agent_OpenClaw Prompt Execution/analysis-overview.md","limit":100}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":157577,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":157577,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775868673322}}
{"type":"message","id":"8b8593d9","parentId":"fbecf421","timestamp":"2026-04-11T00:51:31.098Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_sDeIeq0DbzhMmLIJdYctUE6M","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# OpenClaw System Analysis - Overview\n\n> **Generated by**: Level 0 Overview Agent (overview-architect)  \n> **Date**: Analysis Phase  \n> **Source**: openclaw-complete-manifest.md  \n> **Purpose**: Context briefings for Level 1 Domain Expert Agents\n\n---\n\n## 1. SYSTEM MAP\n\n### 1.1 High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                           OPENCLAW AI AGENT SYSTEM                          │\n│                              (Agent-ID: andrew-main)                        │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                                                                             │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐    ┌─────────────────┐         │\n│  │   CHANNELS      │    │   SUB-AGENTS    │    │   EXTERNAL      │         │\n│  │                 │    │                 │    │   SERVICES      │         │\n│  │ • webchat       │◄──►│ • architect     │    │                 │         │\n│  │ • terminal      │    │ • planner       │◄──►│ • Gemini Search │         │\n│  │ • Telegram      │    │ • code-reviewer │    │ • wttr.in       │         │\n│  │                 │    │ • security      │    │ • Open-Meteo    │         │\n│  └────────┬────────┘    │ • python-rev    │    │ • GitHub        │         │\n│           │             │ • knowledge-cur │    │ • Obsidian      │         │\n│           │             └─────────────────┘    └─────────────────┘         │\n│           │                                                                 │\n│           ▼                                                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                     NODE.JS/TYPESCRIPT CORE                          │   │\n│  │  (OpenClaw Gateway, Session Management, Tool Integration)            │   │\n│  └────────┬──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────────────┘   │\n│           │                              │                                 │\n│           ▼                              ▼                                 │\n│  ┌─────────────────┐          ┌─────────────────┐                         │\n│  │  RUST ECC CRATES │          │  REGISTRY SYSTEM │                         │\n│  │                  │          │                  │                         │\n│  │ • ecc-runtime    │          │ • agents.yaml    │                         │\n│  │ • memory-compact │          │ • skills.yaml    │                         │\n│  │ • tool-registry  │          │ • hooks.yaml     │                         │\n│  └────────┬─────────┘          └────────┬─────────┘                         │\n│           │                             │                                  │\n│           │    ┌────────────────────────┘                                  │\n│           │    │                                                            │\n│           ▼    ▼                                                            │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                      AUTOMATION & MEMORY LAYER                       │   │\n│  │  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐              │   │\n│  │  │   HOOKS      │  │ POWERSHELL   │  │ SECOND BRAIN │              │   │\n│  │  │              │  │              │  │              │              │   │\n│  │  │ • session-   │  │ • sync       │  │ • PARA       │              │   │\n│  │  │   start      │  │ • permissions│  │   structure  │              │   │\n│  │  │ • session-   │  │ • backup     │  │ • Obsidian   │              │   │\n│  │  │   end        │  │              │  │   sync       │              │   │\n│  │  │ • review-    │  │              │  │              │              │   │\n│  │  │   post-exec  │  │              │  │              │              │   │\n│  │  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘              │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n│                                                                             │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### 1.2 Data Flow Diagram\n\n```\nUser Request → Channel Handler → Session Manager → Skill Registry Lookup\n                                                    │\n                    ┌───────────────────────────────┼───────────────┐\n                    │                               │               │\n                    ▼                               ▼               ▼\n            Sub-Agent Spawn                  Tool Execution    Memory Log\n                    │                               │               │\n                    ▼                               ▼               ▼\n            ACP Runtime                    Rust Tool Registry  Daily Logs\n            (if external)                        │            (memory/)\n                                                 ▼\n                                          ECC Runtime\n                                          (Conversation)\n                                                 │\n                                                 ▼\n                                          Hook Trigger\n                                                 │\n                    ┌────────────────────────────┼────────────────────┐\n                    │                            │                    │\n                    ▼                            ▼                    ▼\n            Session-End Hook           Review Post-Exec      Second Brain Sync\n                    │                     Hook (cron: 5min)\n                    ▼\n            Memory Compaction\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. DOMAIN BOUNDARIES\n\n### 2.1 Domain Overview Table\n\n\n[468 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775868691090}}
