{"type":"message","id":"7d4def5f","parentId":"6e08f556","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:06:21.137Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Jetzt die zwei wichtigen Dateien (Second Brain Audit und Action Checklist), dann den Partial Merge für Recommendations.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_pNgPmi7ERqldUXJ6rNsyQvPG","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 03-04-2026\ntype: reference\nstatus: active\ntags: [second-brain, audit, findings, para, memory, critique]\nsource: vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/Kimi_Agent_OpenClaw Prompt Execution/phase1-findings-second-brain.md\noverlap_checked: true\noverlap_with: []\noverlap_percentage: 0%\nmigration_strategy: ADD\nreason: Externe Audit unseres SecondBrain - kritische Findings\n---\n\n# Second Brain + Memory System: External Audit Findings\n\n> **Analyzed by**: Agent E1 (Memory System Analyzer)  \n> **Scope**: PARA structure, memory/ directory, MEMORY.md, daily logs, sync pipeline\n\n---\n\n## Intention vs. Reality\n\n### Was das System SOLLTE tun\n\n| Funktion | Erwartung |\n|----------|-----------|\n| **PARA Structure** | Wissen in Projects, Areas, Resources, Archive organisieren |\n| **Memory Recall** | Vorherigen Kontext vor Antworten abrufen |\n| **Self-Improving** | Aus Korrekturen lernen |\n| **Daily Logs** | Transienten Session-Kontext capturen |\n| **Sync Pipeline** | Second Brain (Obsidian) synchron halten |\n\n### Was es TATSÄCHLICH tut\n\n| Funktion | Realität | Problem |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| **PARA Structure** | 90% leer - 1 project, 3 areas, 3 resources | Nutzloser Overhead |\n| **Memory Recall** | `memory_search` Tool existiert **nicht** | Unmöglich |\n| **Self-Improving** | \"Implizit bei Korrekturen\" - keine Mechanik definiert | Passiert nicht |\n| **Daily Logs** | 7 Logs duplizieren manifest changelog | Write-only |\n| **Sync Pipeline** | 5-Minuten Sync ohne Begründung | Overkill |\n\n---\n\n## Kritische Fehler\n\n### Error 1: Hallucinated `memory_search` Tool\n- **Location**: manifest.md Section 7.4\n- **Claim**: \"Mandatory before answering questions about previous work\"\n- **Reality**: Tool ist nirgends definiert\n- **Severity**: **CRITICAL**\n\n### Error 2: Self-Improving Feedback Loop Undefined\n- **Trigger**: \"implizit bei Korrekturen\"\n- **Missing**: Detection, Storage, Recall Mechanismen\n- **Reality**: Aspirational, nicht operational\n- **Severity**: **HIGH**\n\n### Error 3: No Curation Process\n- **Ratio**: 7 daily logs → 2 MEMORY.md Einträge\n- **Loss**: 71% der geloggten Informationen gehen verloren\n- **Severity**: **HIGH**\n\n---\n\n## Inefficiencies\n\n### 1. Massive Information Duplication\n**Beispiel:** PowerShell Fixes dokumentiert in:\n- MEMORY.md\n- 2026-03-31.md\n- Manifest Changelog\n\n**Problem**: Änderungen erfordern Updates in 3+ Dateien\n\n### 2. 5-Minute Sync Frequency Unjustified\n- **Frequenz**: 288 mal/Tag\n- **Reale Änderungen**: ~1/Tag\n- **Problem**: Wasted compute, potential race conditions\n\n### 3. PARA Structure Overhead\n- **Struktur**: 4-Level Taxonomie\n- **Content**: Minimal\n- **Ratio**: Overhead > Value\n\n---\n\n## Empfohlene Fixes\n\n| Issue | Lösung | Priorität |\n|-------|--------|-----------|\n| `memory_search` | Tool implementieren oder Dokumentation korrigieren | P0 |\n| Self-Improving | Explizite Mechanik definieren | P1 |\n| Curation | Definierter Prozess: Daily → MEMORY.md | P1 |\n| Sync | On-demand oder hourly statt 5-min | P2 |\n| PARA | Struktur vereinfachen oder content erhöhen | P2 |\n\n---\n\n## Verwandte Dokumente\n\n- [[_MOC-Knowledge|Knowledge MOC]] → Übergeordnete Wissensstruktur\n- [[MEMORY]] → Unsere Memory-Strategie\n- [[openclaw-action-checklist|Action Checklist]] → Konkrete Fix-Tasks\n\n---\n\n**Status**: Audit Complete - 3 Critical Issues identified  \n**Next Step**: Fixes implementieren (siehe Action Checklist)","path":"SecondBrain/03-Knowledge/References/second-brain-audit-findings.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_SWTWshhBZkw71KTqybPsyyIX","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"---\ndate: 03-04-2026\ntype: checklist\nstatus: active\ntags: [openclaw, action-items, checklist, todo, prioritized]\nsource: vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/Kimi_Agent_OpenClaw Prompt Execution/action-items-prioritized.md\noverlap_checked: true\noverlap_with: [openclaw-renovation.md]\noverlap_percentage: 30%\nmigration_strategy: ADD\nreason: Konkrete Checkbox-Struktur ergänzt Projekt-Phasen\n---\n\n# OpenClaw System: Prioritized Action Checklist\n\n> Generated by: Agent P3 (Project Lead)  \n> Zweck: Priorisierte, abhakbare Checkliste für inkrementelle Fixes\n\n---\n\n## How to Use\n\n### Progress Tracking\n```\n- [ ] Not started\n- [-] In progress\n- [x] Completed\n- [?] Blocked (Grund angeben)\n```\n\n### Für LLMs\n- Vor Arbeit: Checkliste lesen\n- Eine Sache komplett fertig machen\n- Fortschritt dokumentieren\n- Bei Unklarheit: Fragen!\n\n---\n\n## Priority 1: Critical (Fix Immediately)\n\n### P1-1: Fix Tool Parameter Naming Mismatch\n- [ ] **Investigate** exact location of parameter validation\n  - Domain: Node.js Core / Tool Registry\n  - Files: Tool registry code, hook handlers, middleware\n  \n- [ ] **Determine** canonical parameter name\n  - Decision: snake_case vs camelCase?\n  \n- [ ] **Update** ALL locations to match\n  - Files: Manifest, skill files, tool schema\n\n**Verwandt**: [[openclaw-edit-bug-analysis|Technische Analyse]]\n\n---\n\n### P1-2: Clarify Rust ECC Code Location\n- [ ] **Verify** if Rust code exists in external repository\n  - Check: `everything-claude-code-main` directory\n  \n- [ ] **Update** manifest with clarification\n  - Note: \"Rust ECC in external repo: [path]\" OR \"Rust ECC planned\"\n\n---\n\n### P1-3: Verify Hook System Status\n- [ ] **Clarify** hook system intent with operator\n  - Question: Automatic, manual, or planned?\n  \n- [ ] **Update** manifest based on clarification\n  - Options: \"In Progress\", \"Planned\", \"Manual Protocols\"\n\n---\n\n## Priority 2: High (Fix This Week)\n\n### P2-1: Implement memory_search Tool OR Fix Documentation\n- [ ] **Option A**: Implement actual tool\n  - Search MEMORY.md + memory/*.md\n  - Return relevant snippets\n  \n- [ ] **Option B**: Remove from documentation\n  - If not implemented, don't claim it's mandatory\n\n**Verwandt**: [[second-brain-audit-findings|Audit Findings]]\n\n---\n\n### P2-2: Define Self-Improving Mechanism\n- [ ] **Design** correction detection\n- [ ] **Design** storage format\n- [ ] **Design** recall mechanism\n- [ ] **Implement** feedback loop\n\n**Verwandt**: [[second-brain-audit-findings|Audit Findings]]\n\n---\n\n### P2-3: Create Curation Process (Daily → MEMORY.md)\n- [ ] **Define** criteria: What gets promoted?\n- [ ] **Define** frequency: Weekly? After each session?\n- [ ] **Implement** review workflow\n- [ ] **Document** process\n\n**Verwandt**: [[second-brain-audit-findings|Audit Findings]]\n\n---\n\n### P2-4: Optimize Sync Frequency\n- [ ] **Evaluate** current 5-minute sync\n- [ ] **Change** to: On-demand OR hourly OR file-watcher\n- [ ] **Measure** impact\n\n**Verwandt**: [[second-brain-audit-findings|Audit Findings]]\n\n---\n\n## Priority 3: Medium (Fix This Month)\n\n### P3-1: Simplify PARA Structure OR Add Content\n- [ ] **Audit** current usage\n- [ ] **Decide**: Simplify structure OR populate content\n- [ ] **Implement** decision\n\n---\n\n### P3-2: Consolidate Duplicate Information\n- [ ] **Identify** all duplicates (PowerShell fixes, etc.)\n- [ ] **Choose** single source of truth\n- [ ] **Update** all references\n\n---\n\n### P3-3: Verify Registry Usage\n- [ ] **Check** if all 18 skills in skills.yaml are actively used\n- [ ] **Check** if hooks.yaml actually triggers handlers\n- [ ] **Document** findings\n\n---\n\n## Verwandte Dokumente\n\n- [[openclaw-renovation|Renovierung Projekt]] → Übergeordnete Phasen\n- [[openclaw-edit-bug-analysis|Edit-Bug Analysis]] → P1-1 Details\n- [[second-brain-audit-findings|Second Brain Audit]] → P2-1 bis P2-4 Kontext\n- [[openclaw-system-architecture|System Architecture]] → Domain-Übersicht\n\n---\n\n**Original**: action-items-prioritized.md (15 KB)  \n**Unterschied zu Renovierung**: Konkrete Checkboxen vs. Phasen-Übersicht","path":"SecondBrain/03-Knowledge/References/openclaw-action-checklist.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":93100,"output":2367,"cacheRead":66304,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":161771,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775869498576}}
