{"type":"message","id":"e552db86","parentId":"804f1d58","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:11:11.742Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Lass mich alle 5 Dateien aus Batch 2 nochmal durchgehen und prüfen, ob die Inhalte korrekt und vollständig sind.\n\nDie 5 Dateien sind:\n1. openclaw-edit-bug-analysis.md\n2. openclaw-system-architecture.md\n3. second-brain-audit-findings.md\n4. openclaw-action-checklist.md\n5. openclaw-analysis-index.md (Index)\n\nIch sollte jede Datei lesen und auf folgendes prüfen:\n- YAML-Frontmatter korrekt?\n- Inhalt vollständig?\n- WikiLinks funktionieren?\n- Keine Platzhalter oder \"...\"?\n- Backup-Verweis vorhanden?","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Ich prüfe alle 5 Dateien aus Batch 2 auf Korrektheit..."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_vjoepnmZuNSpwSHFGaBFwW4K","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"SecondBrain/03-Knowledge/References/openclaw-edit-bug-analysis.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_Khj1UBdj4b0AipnZZjnVRZZn","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"SecondBrain/03-Knowledge/References/openclaw-system-architecture.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_Q6whBy4JaDJTQz9FVgpw2Asp","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"SecondBrain/03-Knowledge/References/second-brain-audit-findings.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":166964,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":166964,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775869858568}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5e9448b","parentId":"e552db86","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:11:11.770Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_vjoepnmZuNSpwSHFGaBFwW4K","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 03-04-2026\ntype: reference\nstatus: active\ntags: [openclaw, bugfix, edit-tool, analysis, root-cause]\nsource: vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/Kimi_Agent_OpenClaw Prompt Execution/bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md\noverlap_checked: true\noverlap_with: [edit-tool-workaround.md]\noverlap_percentage: 10%\nmigration_strategy: ADD\nreason: Technische Root-Cause-Analyse ergänzt den praktischen Workaround\n---\n\n# OpenClaw Edit-Tool Bug: Root Cause Analysis\n\n> **Schweregrad**: Medium-High  \n> **Typ**: Parameter Naming Mismatch (Dokumentation vs. Implementation)  \n> **Impact**: Tool calls fail when parameter name doesn't match expected schema\n\n---\n\n## Das Kernproblem\n\nFehlermeldung: `[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText`\n\n**Mismatch zwischen:**\n| Quelle | Parameter Name | Kontext |\n|--------|---------------|---------|\n| **Manifest Dokumentation** | `new_string` | Section 5.3 |\n| **Error Message** | `newText` | Runtime validation |\n| **Tool Schema (impliziert)** | Likely `new_string` | Based on convention |\n\n---\n\n## Root Cause Hypotheses\n\n### 1. Schema Translation Layer Issue (Wahrscheinlichst)\n- Tool schema definiert Parameter als `new_string` (snake_case)\n- Middleware konvertiert zu camelCase für Consumer\n- Error validation erwartet `newText`, aber Tool caller sendet `new_string`\n\n### 2. Inconsistent Schema Versions\n- Dokumentation referenziert eine Version (`new_string`)\n- Runtime nutzt andere Version (`newText`)\n- Könnte während Migration/API Update passiert sein\n\n### 3. Hook Interference\n- `review:post_execution` hook oder andere Middleware transformiert Parameter\n\n---\n\n## Evidence\n\n**Aus Manifest (Line 233):**\n```markdown\n**NIE**: `edit` ohne `new_string` Parameter\n```\n\n**Aus multi-agent-analysis-prompt.md:**\n- Line 403: Scope erwähnt explizit: `Diagnose '[tools] edit failed: Missing required parameter: newText'`\n- Line 409: \"Identify where `new_string` parameter is missing\"\n\n---\n\n## Implementierungsvorschlag\n\n**Option C (Empfohlen): Support beide mit Deprecation**\n\n```typescript\ninterface EditFileParams {\n  file_path: string;\n  old_string: string;\n  new_string?: string;\n  newText?: string;  // Deprecated\n}\n\nfunction validateEditParams(params: EditFileParams) {\n  const newContent = params.new_string ?? params.newText;\n  \n  if (!newContent) {\n    throw new Error('Missing required parameter: new_string (or deprecated newText)');\n  }\n  \n  if (params.newText && !params.new_string) {\n    console.warn('Deprecation warning: newText is deprecated, use new_string');\n  }\n  \n  return { ...params, new_string: newContent };\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Verwandte Dokumente\n\n- [[edit-tool-workaround|Praktischer Workaround]] → Was User JETZT tun können\n- [[openclaw-renovation|Renovierung]] → Langfristige Fix-Planung\n- [[openclaw-action-checklist|Action Checklist]] → Konkrete Fix-Tasks\n\n---\n\n**Original:** bugfix-edit-failed-analysis.md (9 KB)  \n**Status**: Root-Cause identifiziert, Fix pending"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775869871763}}
{"type":"message","id":"bfbc26b7","parentId":"f5e9448b","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:11:11.775Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_Khj1UBdj4b0AipnZZjnVRZZn","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 03-04-2026\ntype: reference\nstatus: active\ntags: [openclaw, architecture, system-analysis, domains]\nsource: vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/Kimi_Agent_OpenClaw Prompt Execution/analysis-overview.md\noverlap_checked: true\noverlap_with: [openclaw-renovation.md]\noverlap_percentage: 30%\nmigration_strategy: ADD\nreason: Detaillierte Architektur-Analyse ergänzt Projekt-Übersicht\n---\n\n# OpenClaw System Architecture: Domain Analysis\n\n> Generated by: Level 0 Overview Agent  \n> Zweck: Context briefings for Domain Expert Agents\n\n---\n\n## High-Level Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    OPENCLAW AI AGENT                        │\n│                     (Agent-ID: andrew-main)                 │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  CHANNELS        │  SUB-AGENTS      │  EXTERNAL SERVICES   │\n│  • webchat       │  • architect     │  • Gemini Search     │\n│  • terminal      │  • planner       │  • wttr.in           │\n│  • Telegram      │  • code-reviewer │  • GitHub            │\n│                  │  • security      │  • Obsidian          │\n└────────┬─────────┴──────────────────┴──────────────────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              NODE.JS/TYPESCRIPT CORE                        │\n│         (Gateway, Session Management, Tools)                │\n└────────┬──────────────────────────────┬────────────────────┘\n         │                              │\n    ┌────▼─────┐                ┌───────▼────────┐\n    │ RUST ECC │                │ YAML REGISTRY  │\n    │  CRATES  │                │                │\n    │          │                │ • agents.yaml  │\n    │ • runtime│                │ • skills.yaml  │\n    │ • memory │                │ • hooks.yaml   │\n    │ • tools  │                │                │\n    └────┬─────┘                └────────────────┘\n         │\n         ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              AUTOMATION & MEMORY LAYER                      │\n│  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐                  │\n│  │   HOOKS  │  │POWERSHELL│  │2nd BRAIN │                  │\n│  │          │  │          │  │          │                  │\n│  │• session-│  │• sync    │  │• PARA    │                  │\n│  │  start   │  │• backup  │  │• Obsidian│                  │\n│  │• session-│  │          │  │  sync    │                  │\n│  │  end     │  │          │  │          │                  │\n│  └──────────┘  └──────────┘  └──────────┘                  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Die 5 Domains\n\n| Domain | Technologie | Verantwortung | Key Files |\n|--------|-------------|---------------|-----------|\n| **A: Rust ECC** | Rust | Core runtime, memory, tools | `crates/*` (60+ Tests) |\n| **B: Node.js Core** | TypeScript | Gateway, sessions, channels | Root Gateway |\n| **C: YAML Registry** | YAML | Config, agents, skills, hooks | `registry/*.yaml` |\n| **D: PowerShell + Hooks** | PowerShell/Markdown | Automation, events | `hooks/`, `*.ps1` |\n| **E: Second Brain** | Markdown | Knowledge, PARA, logs | `memory/`, `second-brain/` |\n\n---\n\n## Interface Boundaries\n\n### A ↔ B: Rust ↔ Node.js\n- FFI bindings oder WASM (nicht spezifiziert)\n- Tool Registry exposed zu TypeScript\n- ECC Runtime managed conversation state\n\n### B ↔ C: Node.js ↔ YAML Registry\n- agents.yaml loaded at startup\n- skills.yaml scanned before each response\n- hooks.yaml triggers handlers\n\n### B ↔ D: Node.js ↔ Hooks/PowerShell\n- session:start → hooks/session-start.md\n- session:end → hooks/session-end.md\n- Cron triggers PowerShell scripts\n\n### B ↔ E: Node.js ↔ Second Brain\n- Daily logs: `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md`\n- Curated: MEMORY.md\n- Sync: 5-minute cron (questionable)\n\n---\n\n## Kritische Issues (Aus Analyse)\n\n| Issue | Domain | Schweregrad | Status |\n|-------|--------|-------------|--------|\n| **Edit-Tool Parameter Mismatch** | B | **CRITICAL** | Unresolved |\n| Hook Activation unklar | D | HIGH | Unverified |\n| Registry Usage unverifiziert | C | HIGH | Unknown |\n| MCP Adapter \"in Arbeit\" | A | MEDIUM | In Progress |\n\n---\n\n## Verwandte Dokumente\n\n- [[openclaw-edit-bug-analysis|Edit-Bug Analysis]] → Details zu Critical Issue\n- [[openclaw-renovation|Renovierung Projekt]] → Projekt-Phasen\n- [[second-brain-audit-findings|Second Brain Audit]] → Domain E Analysis\n- [[claw-code-integration-index|Claw-Code Specs]] → Rust Integration\n- [[openclaw-action-checklist|Action Checklist]] → Konkrete Tasks\n\n---\n\n**Original:** analysis-overview.md (30 KB)  \n**Unterschied zu Renovierung**: Fokus auf Domain-Analyse statt Projekt-Management"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775869871770}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a571a1f","parentId":"bfbc26b7","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:11:11.781Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_Q6whBy4JaDJTQz9FVgpw2Asp","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\ndate: 03-04-2026\ntype: reference\nstatus: active\ntags: [second-brain, audit, findings, para, memory, critique]\nsource: vault-archive/Main_Obsidian_Vault/Kimi_Agent_OpenClaw Prompt Execution/phase1-findings-second-brain.md\noverlap_checked: true\noverlap_with: []\noverlap_percentage: 0%\nmigration_strategy: ADD\nreason: Externe Audit unseres SecondBrain - kritische Findings\n---\n\n# Second Brain + Memory System: External Audit Findings\n\n> **Analyzed by**: Agent E1 (Memory System Analyzer)  \n> **Scope**: PARA structure, memory/ directory, MEMORY.md, daily logs, sync pipeline\n\n---\n\n## Intention vs. Reality\n\n### Was das System SOLLTE tun\n\n| Funktion | Erwartung |\n|----------|-----------|\n| **PARA Structure** | Wissen in Projects, Areas, Resources, Archive organisieren |\n| **Memory Recall** | Vorherigen Kontext vor Antworten abrufen |\n| **Self-Improving** | Aus Korrekturen lernen |\n| **Daily Logs** | Transienten Session-Kontext capturen |\n| **Sync Pipeline** | Second Brain (Obsidian) synchron halten |\n\n### Was es TATSÄCHLICH tut\n\n| Funktion | Realität | Problem |\n|----------|----------|---------|\n| **PARA Structure** | 90% leer - 1 project, 3 areas, 3 resources | Nutzloser Overhead |\n| **Memory Recall** | `memory_search` Tool existiert **nicht** | Unmöglich |\n| **Self-Improving** | \"Implizit bei Korrekturen\" - keine Mechanik definiert | Passiert nicht |\n| **Daily Logs** | 7 Logs duplizieren manifest changelog | Write-only |\n| **Sync Pipeline** | 5-Minuten Sync ohne Begründung | Overkill |\n\n---\n\n## Kritische Fehler\n\n### Error 1: Hallucinated `memory_search` Tool\n- **Location**: manifest.md Section 7.4\n- **Claim**: \"Mandatory before answering questions about previous work\"\n- **Reality**: Tool ist nirgends definiert\n- **Severity**: **CRITICAL**\n\n### Error 2: Self-Improving Feedback Loop Undefined\n- **Trigger**: \"implizit bei Korrekturen\"\n- **Missing**: Detection, Storage, Recall Mechanismen\n- **Reality**: Aspirational, nicht operational\n- **Severity**: **HIGH**\n\n### Error 3: No Curation Process\n- **Ratio**: 7 daily logs → 2 MEMORY.md Einträge\n- **Loss**: 71% der geloggten Informationen gehen verloren\n- **Severity**: **HIGH**\n\n---\n\n## Inefficiencies\n\n### 1. Massive Information Duplication\n**Beispiel:** PowerShell Fixes dokumentiert in:\n- MEMORY.md\n- 2026-03-31.md\n- Manifest Changelog\n\n**Problem**: Änderungen erfordern Updates in 3+ Dateien\n\n### 2. 5-Minute Sync Frequency Unjustified\n- **Frequenz**: 288 mal/Tag\n- **Reale Änderungen**: ~1/Tag\n- **Problem**: Wasted compute, potential race conditions\n\n### 3. PARA Structure Overhead\n- **Struktur**: 4-Level Taxonomie\n- **Content**: Minimal\n- **Ratio**: Overhead > Value\n\n---\n\n## Empfohlene Fixes\n\n| Issue | Lösung | Priorität |\n|-------|--------|-----------|\n| `memory_search` | Tool implementieren oder Dokumentation korrigieren | P0 |\n| Self-Improving | Explizite Mechanik definieren | P1 |\n| Curation | Definierter Prozess: Daily → MEMORY.md | P1 |\n| Sync | On-demand oder hourly statt 5-min | P2 |\n| PARA | Struktur vereinfachen oder content erhöhen | P2 |\n\n---\n\n## Verwandte Dokumente\n\n- [[_MOC-Knowledge|Knowledge MOC]] → Übergeordnete Wissensstruktur\n- [[MEMORY]] → Unsere Memory-Strategie\n- [[openclaw-action-checklist|Action Checklist]] → Konkrete Fix-Tasks\n\n---\n\n**Status**: Audit Complete - 3 Critical Issues identified  \n**Next Step**: Fixes implementieren (siehe Action Checklist)"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775869871775}}
