{"type":"message","id":"034bccc9","parentId":"364c1894","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:50:08.595Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the plan-feature skill to include this redundancy check as part of Phase 0.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Jetzt erweitere ich den **plan-feature Skill**:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_fAypGayQvaqJQxSZAAQ7N0hA","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"skills/plan-feature/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":180004,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":180004,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775872198488}}
{"type":"message","id":"1f310086","parentId":"034bccc9","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:50:08.619Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_fAypGayQvaqJQxSZAAQ7N0hA","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: plan-feature\ndescription: Turn a feature idea into a phased implementation plan using vertical slices (tracer bullets). Use when user wants to break down a feature, create an implementation plan, plan phases, or mentions \"tracer bullets\" or \"vertical slices\".\n---\n\n# Plan Feature\n\nTransform a feature idea into a phased implementation plan using **vertical slices** (tracer bullets). Output is a Markdown file in `./plans/`.\n\n## Quick Start\n\n1. Describe your feature idea\n2. I'll explore the codebase (if needed)\n3. We'll identify durable architectural decisions\n4. I'll propose vertical slices\n5. You review and approve\n6. Plan saved to `./plans/<feature-name>.md`\n\n## What are Vertical Slices?\n\n**Vertical slices** are thin, complete paths through ALL layers:\n\n```\n❌ HORIZONTAL (bad):\nPhase 1: Write all tests\nPhase 2: Build all API\nPhase 3: Build all UI\n\n✅ VERTICAL (tracer bullets):\nPhase 1: ONE feature end-to-end (DB→API→UI→Tests)\nPhase 2: NEXT feature end-to-end\nPhase 3: NEXT feature end-to-end\n```\n\nEach slice is **demoable on its own**.\n\n## Process\n\n### 1. Confirm Feature Scope\n\nTell me:\n- What problem are you solving?\n- Who is the user?\n- What does \"done\" look like?\n\n### 2. Explore Codebase\n\nIf needed, I'll explore to understand:\n- Current architecture\n- Existing patterns\n- Integration points\n\n### 3. Identify Durable Decisions\n\nBefore slicing, we'll lock in:\n\n| Decision Type | Examples |\n|--------------|----------|\n| Routes | URL patterns, API endpoints |\n| Schema | Database tables, data models |\n| Auth | Authentication/authorization approach |\n| Boundaries | Third-party service interfaces |\n\nThese go in the plan header.\n\n### 4. Draft Vertical Slices\n\nI'll break the feature into **tracer bullet phases**:\n\n<vertical-slice-rules>\n- Each slice: narrow but COMPLETE through all layers\n- Each slice: demoable/verifiable on its own\n- Prefer many thin slices over few thick ones\n- NO specific filenames or function names (will change)\n- YES durable decisions: routes, schema shapes, model names\n</vertical-slice-rules>\n\n### 5. Quiz You\n\nI'll present phases as a numbered list:\n\n| Phase | Title | User Stories Covered |\n|-------|-------|---------------------|\n| 1 | Basic user creation | #1, #2 |\n| 2 | Email verification | #3 |\n| 3 | Password reset | #4, #5 |\n\n**You decide:**\n- Granularity (too coarse / too fine?)\n- Merge or split phases?\n- Reordering?\n\n### 6. Write Plan File\n\nCreates `./plans/` if missing. Saves plan as Markdown.\n\n## Plan Template\n\n```markdown\n# Plan: <Feature Name>\n\n> Source: <brief description or link>\n\n## Durable Architectural Decisions\n\n| Decision | Choice |\n|----------|--------|\n| Routes | ... |\n| Schema | ... |\n| Key Models | ... |\n| Auth | ... |\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: <Title>\n\n**User stories:** <list>\n\n### What to Build\n\nConcise description of this vertical slice. Describe end-to-end behavior, not layer-by-layer implementation.\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Criterion 1\n- [ ] Criterion 2\n- [ ] Criterion 3\n\n### Technical Notes\n\n- Durable decisions used\n- Integration points\n- Testing approach\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: <Title>\n\n...\n```\n\n## Example Session\n\n**You:** \"I want to add user authentication\"\n\n**Me:** [Explores codebase, identifies durable decisions]\n\n**Me:** \"Here's my proposed breakdown:\n\n| Phase | Title | Stories |\n|-------|-------|---------|\n| 1 | Basic login form | User can enter credentials |\n| 2 | Session management | User stays logged in |\n| 3 | Registration flow | New user can sign up |\n\nDoes this granularity feel right? Should any phases be merged or split?\"\n\n**You:** \"Split phase 3 into email verification and registration\"\n\n**Me:** [Updates plan, writes to `./plans/user-authentication.md`]\n\n## Checklist for Me\n\n- [ ] Feature scope confirmed\n- [ ] Codebase explored (if needed)\n- [ ] Durable decisions identified\n- [ ] Vertical slices drafted\n- [ ] User approved breakdown\n- [ ] Plan written to `./plans/`\n\n## See Also\n\n- [tdd-loop](tdd-loop/SKILL.md) – Execute phases with TDD\n- [grill-me](grill-me/SKILL.md) – Stress-test the plan first\n- Matt Pocock's prd-to-plan inspiration\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775872208611}}
{"type":"message","id":"889906aa","parentId":"1f310086","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:50:56.069Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to add a Phase 0 to the plan-feature skill that includes a redundancy check before starting any feature planning. This will help prevent the issue we just had.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"tool_j4elFVeaIQV0JyWDWZcCwQUe","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"skills/plan-feature/SKILL.md","old_string":"## Process\n\n### 1. Confirm Feature Scope","new_string":"## Process\n\n### Phase 0: Redundancy Check (NEW - Critical)\n\n**Before starting any feature, check if it already exists:**\n\n| Check | Location | Command/Method |\n|-------|----------|----------------|\n| Workarounds | `How-To/` | `memory_search \"workaround\"` |\n| Skills | `skills/` + `registry/skills.yaml` | Read registry/skills.yaml |\n| Scripts | `00-Meta/Scripts/` | List directory |\n| Documentation | `MEMORY.md` + `_MOC-Knowledge.md` | Search memory |\n| Projects | `02-Projects/` | Check _MOC-Projects.md |\n| Tools | `TOOLS.md` | Read TOOLS.md |\n\n**If unsure:** Ask user \"Do we already have something for this?\"\n\n**Lesson Learned:** 11-04-2026 - Created duplicate SafeEdit.psm1 when edit-tool-workaround.md already existed.\n\n---\n\n### 1. Confirm Feature Scope"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":78812,"output":296,"cacheRead":101120,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":180228,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775872208633}}
{"type":"message","id":"8c6b271f","parentId":"889906aa","timestamp":"2026-04-11T01:50:56.091Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_j4elFVeaIQV0JyWDWZcCwQUe","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in skills/plan-feature/SKILL.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  35 Each slice is **demoable on its own**.\n  36 \n  37 ## Process\n  38 \n+ 39 ### Phase 0: Redundancy Check (NEW - Critical)\n+ 40 \n+ 41 **Before starting any feature, check if it already exists:**\n+ 42 \n+ 43 | Check | Location | Command/Method |\n+ 44 |-------|----------|----------------|\n+ 45 | Workarounds | `How-To/` | `memory_search \"workaround\"` |\n+ 46 | Skills | `skills/` + `registry/skills.yaml` | Read registry/skills.yaml |\n+ 47 | Scripts | `00-Meta/Scripts/` | List directory |\n+ 48 | Documentation | `MEMORY.md` + `_MOC-Knowledge.md` | Search memory |\n+ 49 | Projects | `02-Projects/` | Check _MOC-Projects.md |\n+ 50 | Tools | `TOOLS.md` | Read TOOLS.md |\n+ 51 \n+ 52 **If unsure:** Ask user \"Do we already have something for this?\"\n+ 53 \n+ 54 **Lesson Learned:** 11-04-2026 - Created duplicate SafeEdit.psm1 when edit-tool-workaround.md already existed.\n+ 55 \n+ 56 ---\n+ 57 \n  39 ### 1. Confirm Feature Scope\n  40 \n  41 Tell me:\n  42 - What problem are you solving?\n     ...","firstChangedLine":39},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775872256086}}
